This could just be because I don't understand Clojure syntax that well, but I've always used `shell-bolt-spec` and `shell-spout-spec` like [this](http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/konarkmodi/Presentations/blob/master/notebooks/NRT-Slides.ipynb):

```clojure
(def wordcount
   [
    ;; spout configuration
    {"word-spout" (shell-spout-spec
          ["python" "words.py"]
          ["word"]
          )
    }
    ;; bolt configuration
    {"count-bolt" (shell-bolt-spec
           {"word-spout" :shuffle}
           ["python" "wordcount.py"]
           ["word" "count"]
           :p 2
           )
    }
  ]
)
```
where the first element after `shell-spout-spec` (and the second after `shell-bolt-spec`) is a list much like one would pass to `subprocess.call` in Python.  The official Clojure DSL documentation doesn't show it this way (and in fact doesn't show `shell-spout-spec` at all), but I think this is easier to read (and I know it actually works).

