The reason it is under `bower_components` is because i install bootstrap using `bower install boostrap-sass-official` in Ruby. By using bower, it allows me to create a bower.json file where i can always grab the latest versions of bootstrap by typing `bower install` for a project.

``` javascript
  "main": "theme/style.css",
  "devDependencies": {
    "bootstrap-sass-official": "latest",
    "bourbon": "latest",
    "fontawesome": "latest"    
  }
```

Like i stated in my parent post, it does work using `@import "bootstrap";` in my main scss file, however it sticks all of bootstrap in my main style.css file. I don't want it to do that. I want it in it's own separate file. They only way i can do this, is to do a bower install, then copy the scss files to my sass folder, then set it up in grunt to create a separate file like so

``` javascript
        sass: {
            dist: {
                files: {
                    'theme/style.css': 'sass/style.scss'
                    'theme/css/bootstrap.css': 'sass/bootstrap.scss'
                }
            }
        },
```
The goal is automation. rather than moving files and folders around.

